<h3 class="item__header"><a href="javascript:void(0)">The Long Goodbye</a></h3>

<p class="tertiary">The Long Good-bye is a 1953 novel by Raymond Chandler, centred on his famous detective Philip Marlowe. While some consider it not on the level of The Big Sleep or Farewell, My Lovely, others rank it as the best of his work. It is notable for using hard-boiled detective fiction as a vehicle for social criticism. It is also known for having autobiographical elements that relate to Chandler's life. The novel opens outside a club called The Dancers.</p>

